	<!-- Using inverse indexing to find menuId and menuItemId from path requested by user
		 - Read this file and store it as a map in application context with key is link and
		   value is id of menu and menuItem when starting up
		 - Create tag function for retrieving menuId and menuItemId from link by looking up above map
		 - Every time user requests a link, tag function will lookup the map to find out menuId and menuItemId
		   corresponding to requested link
		 - In left.jsp, using following code to set clicked menu active
		 <li class="item isActiveMenu('info')" id="info">
			<img src="/resources/images/info.png" class="icon_menu" />
			<h3>Quản trị tin tức</h3>
			<ul class="child">
				<li class="isActiveMenuItem('info_1')" id="info_1">
					<img src="/resources/images/add_news.gif" class="bullet_menu" />
					<a href="#">Thêm mới tin</a>
				</li>
				<li class="isActiveMenuItem('info_2')" id="info_2">
					<img src="/resources/images/earth_f.gif" class="bullet_menu" />
					<a href="#">Quản trị tin</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		
		- what isActiveMenu('menu id') function returns 'active' or '' depends on whether current menu was just clicked
		- Similarly, isActiveMenuItem('menu item id') function returns 'active' or '' depends on whether current submenu was just clicked
	 -->
</menus>